# PR Template

## Branch Naming
`<type>/<story-id>-<slug>` — e.g., `feature/DPAY-14337-export-progress`, `bugfix/DPAY-14338-fix-timeout`

## Commit Message
```
<type>(scope): <description>

<STORY-ID>: <Title>

Changes:
- <change 1>
- <change 2>

Tests: <pass count>/<total> passed
Coverage: <percentage>%
```

## PR Description Format
```markdown
## Story
[DPAY-XXXX](https://myjira.disney.com/browse/DPAY-XXXX): <title>

## Type
Feature | Bugfix | Tech Debt

## Changes
- <summary of each change>

## Acceptance Criteria
- [x] <AC 1>
- [x] <AC 2>

## Testing
- Unit tests: X/X passed
- Integration tests: X/X passed
- Coverage: XX%

## Files Changed
- `path/to/file1`
- `path/to/file2`

## Golden Rules Checklist
- [ ] Backward compatible (additive changes only)
- [ ] Test coverage ≥90%
- [ ] No secrets in code
- [ ] Structured logging added
- [ ] Input validation present
- [ ] Error handling complete

## Labels
Type: feature | bugfix | tech-debt
Priority: P0 | P1 | P2 | P3
Component: backend | ui | webapi | mobile
```
